Waterloo Bridge (1940 film)

A Canadian soldier falls in love with a woman in London during WW I, but twists of fate get in the way. Remade in 1940 with Vivien Leigh and Robert Taylor.

Directed by 	Mervyn LeRoy
Produced by 	Sidney Franklin
Written by 	Robert E. Sherwood (play)
S. N. Behrman (screenplay)
Hans Rameau (screenplay)
George Froeschel (screenplay)
Starring 	Robert Taylor
Vivien Leigh
Lucile Watson
Virginia Field
Maria Ouspenskaya
C. Aubrey Smith
